uid4nps

Class UseridPanosInterface

  • java.lang.Object
    • uid4nps.UseridPanosInterface

  • public class UseridPanosInterface
extends java.lang.Object
    This class behaves as a buffer. It prepares valid user-id entries and keeps the in the buffer until either the buffer is full or the timer expires

            java.lang.String UserName,
            java.lang.String FramedIPAddress,
            java.lang.String NASIdentifier)
              throws java.io.IOException
        It adds a valid user-id entry in the corresponding (login/logout) buffer
        Parameters:
        AcctStatusType - "1" means it is an START type of message
        UserName - Username to be used in the user-id XML message
        FramedIPAddress - IP address to be used in the user-id XML message
        NASIdentifier - String with the NAS Identifier. If it is not null it will create a tagged dynamic address object
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • flushEntries

        protected java.lang.String flushEntries()
        Flushes the buffer to the first available PANOSApiConnector device
        Returns:
        The XML response message received by the PANOS device. NULL means we've been unable to send the buffer to any PANOS device

      • loginEntryExists

        protected int loginEntryExists(java.lang.String[] entry,
                   int bufferSize)
        Looks for a given entry in the pending login buffer
        Parameters:
        bufferSize - The size of the buffer
        entry - The entry we're looking in the pending entry buffer
        Returns:
        The index in the login buffer to the element containing the entry we're looking for. If the return value equals to the size of the buffer then it means the entry doesn't exist
